{
  "text": "Its rarity, as well as the difficulty of differential diagnosis with pancreatic solid tumors, makes the preoperative diagnosis complex. The absence of malignant behavior imposes an accurate diagnosis. Therefore, a monitoring or a simple excision, when feasible, is often adequate [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "7327021"
